USA: Repetition is the Mother of Wisdom
It’s almost strange with what student zeal Barack Obama, the president with his reputation for being the smartest, repeats his predecessor’s strategy on the Afghanistan issue, which he himself considered the dumbest.
When he finally sweated out his long-awaited Afghanistan doctrine, it turned out that he wrote it off on the copy paper from the Bush-Iraq scenario three years ago.
Not only did he use the phrase "as in Iraq" several times in the text itself, he even used the name of the Bush Declaration of January 2007 as the name of his own declaration: "New Way Forward", without hesitation.
Three years ago, he criticized the Bush idea - sending fresh troop contingents into the Iraq plagued by civil war - as "irresponsible and, in its aftermath, catastrophic decision".
The following months, however, showed that the Bush strategy, based on military recommendations, was the only possible and, to the extent, very successful, that the news about Iraq today is no longer spoken of at all.
Bush’s reputation was not improved by this, because objectively he left his successor a much more grateful starting position than expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will happen again.
The military again asked him to increase the troop contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of Operation Afghanistan, General Stanley McCristal, who, despite his subordination habits, strongly criticized the indignant gunmen in the White House.
He called for 40,000 soldiers to be able to reverse the situation for the better.
The president hesitated for three months, but did not come up with a better idea and so he deceived the general with 10,000 soldiers.
From Europe, he pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even though he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
What is most problematic about the entire Obama strategy is that he intends to withdraw the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and complete this process in three years. The entire Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the half-increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Despite the brotherly war of recent years, the Iraqi society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterized by the contraindication - no one can be trusted and no agreements are made.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are accustomed to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if formally established correctly, remain only pseudo-buildings behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the unpredictability of the conditions that further complicate the Pakistani and Iranian influences.
The creation of a “capable state”, which is the minimalist goal of the whole operation, is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama’s strategy alienated by its voluntarism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and now it is on the verge of explosion.
To believe that the little soldiers who broke out in the war cry about the "early return" can create a miracle here, only a truly romantic soul that can not be impressed by facts.
From the political point of view, the timing of the withdrawal is purely irresponsible, because the Taliban will accept it as an indirect confession of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in the fighting in Afghanistan is declining.
Europe’s politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is related to the war in the Hindukusch Mountains.
Another possible factor that can radically influence the situation is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the tightened sanctions do not affect the Iranians, the question for the United States is whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question has to be answered in the period when America is stepping up to win the withdrawal from Afghanistan after Obama.
But any solution will also mean a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only consolation for Barack Obama is the fact that there are still three years until the presidential election, and therefore there is still enough time for him to move on to another strategy if it turns out to be a total failure.
