So far, the state has spent about 500,000 per year on all children’s area vaccinations.
The mandatory vaccination was introduced with the so-called Janota package.
Pneumococci cause middle ear inflammation, but also severe infections including cerebral palsy and blood poisoning.
Pneumococcal infections in our country kill up to 28 children up to 10 years old every year after examination in hospitals.
Outside the Czech Republic, compulsory vaccination of children against pneumococcal disease has been introduced in some 40 countries.
Will vaccination be mandatory?
At the same time, it is said that this vaccination could be mandatory in the future.
From January onwards, it will be paid by the insurance companies and will be voluntary.
For example, the head of the Nahlas Civil Society, Rudolf Kalovsky, mentioned that the compulsory vaccination would be better.
