The problem is money.
Other couples give psychological reasons for their hesitation.
Wang, the head of staff, said she only wanted a child because she was also a single child. "We were the center of the family and used to having everyone take care of us.
We’re not used to taking care of others and we don’t really want to.”
Chen Zijian, a 42-year-old who owns a translation company, said it bluntly.
For middle-aged parents with double careers, through which the birth rate drops, he said, it’s about being successful and for that you have to be selfish.
The age group of today’s 20- to 39-year-olds grew up watching their parents struggle during the early days of the Chinese capitalism experiment and they don’t want to live such a life for themselves, he said.
