This initiative aims to draw attention to the importance of helmet use, since it is ultimately the only protective element that can prevent head injuries or even death in the event of a motorcycle accident.
Michelin pointed out that this campaign is part of its commitment to road safety, which “is far more than just designing and manufacturing products that are becoming safer with each passing day,” and reiterated that it also helps with other educational and informational actions to get closer to this goal every day.
This new campaign to promote helmet use on the motorcycle, which runs under the slogan 'To be or not to be', will distribute posters to more than 500 motorcycle workshops in a first phase to achieve the best possible distribution.
In conclusion, Michelin stressed that road safety is "a constant concern" of the company, and precisely for the reason that as a manufacturer of tires for two-wheeled vehicles, it is always committed to one of its main goals must be the development of increasingly safer products.
